<br>
Most guilds do not enjoy support for this option but this may be something <br>
that could get support. 2 guilds arrange to have a 6 member team each at an <br>
entrance to rathe mtns. They both enter at the sametime at opposite ends. The <br>
goal is to kill the other's team captain, determined beforehand. Victory is <br>
determined when a captain is killed or a team surrenders, you can kill off <br>
all the other team's members for instance, except the captain. Corpse <br>
recovery; once killed you are out can recovery corpse and drag to zone and <br>
then leave after recovery. Monk, necro, FD pulls on other party are not <br>
allowed as well as kamikaze pulls. Should take upo a huge amount of time <br>
rathe is huge. PvP is a real challenge remember the duels at equal level with <br>
the 11's just imagine at higher lvl. Only buffs allowed are what your party <br>
can provide. No spell restrictions otherwise. No looting. <br>
<br>
The zone is just one possible and the rules a start point. Since there is a <br>
loot message up now someone looting would inform the entire party. <br>
<br>
Time limits can be set with points awarded based on class and level. At the <br>
end a prize(s) put up by the other guild could be given to the other team <br>
captain. After the exchange of the prize(s) the 2 two teams would exchange 3 <br>
members each and go on a 2 group hunt in the area, drinking could be <br>
encouraged and other interactive activities, drunken giant pulling, etc. <br>
Motto for the event &quot;Start as Enemies. End as Friends.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Belce Gaegwyn Warrior<br>
