<br>
Two guilds would go at it (not necessarily in the same zone).  Each guild would have a brand new level 1 char (type to be established ahead of time) that would be in the process of leveling.  The objective would be to kill this char.  The winner would be whoever leveled their char the highest at the end of the war.  Part of the guild would protect them, another part would be out to kill the leveling char.  The other guild *would* know the name of each guilds leveling char.<br>
<br>
It has some interesting possibilities. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>   <font color=#8E9173>(3/3/00 5:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsevents.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Another Guildwar suggestion</span><hr size=1> I like Belce's idea a lot. I think it has a huge amount of merit and would probably like to do it with the Silver Daggers and someone who is interested. <br>
<br>
The ultimate idea I had in mind was a practice guildwar, that lasted a day. All members of the warring guilds would gather in one spot (probably an open spot like Qeynos Hills or the Plains of Karana) on one day. Then a battle, much like the glorious scenes in Braveheart would ensue. Only members of the warring guilds who are in the designated battle zone would be allowed to be attacked. Any other member being attacked outside of these zones would be compensated by the guild members who made the unauthorized attack.<br>
<br>
But I think for all Guildwars, we need to get a set of rules together that we can all agree on, kind of a Geneva convention for fair and honest warfare. <br>
<br>
Suggestions: <br>
<br>
1) Guild memberships must be fairly equal in size and level. No all 50's level guilds fighting an all 20's level guild. No 100 member guilds pounding on the guild with 20. <br>
2) Exchange of rosters. This would be a list of the guild members that DO NOT wish to participate in the war and so are off limits to attack. There will invariably be some members of each guild that can't or won't participate based on not losing exp. or another reason, and they should be protected. <br>
3) No corpse camping, bind point camping, no in-zone binds, once dead, no returning to the battle (though you could return to watch), etc. <br>
4) No looting of corpses (though this one could be discussed between guild leaders)<br>
<br>
These wars could take place just for fun, for prizes, or for culminations of roleplaying storylines. Who's interested in doing one of these type of wars or one of the type Belce suggested above? What do you think the guidelines should be, what do you think of the guidelines listed?<br>
